 siracha (on the side). Then this recipe came to mind, so I decided to take a part of it and make it into a breakfast meal. So I meltd about a tsp of butter, added a good squirt of siracha to the hot melted butter, stirred, then added two eggs. I scrambled everything together and cooked until the eggs were just done. Serve this with a slice of toast, and you have a great breakfast that is a nice twist on plain scrambled eggs. The butter/siracha combo added a wonderful spicy and velvety texture to the eggs, which are anything but bland. The more siracha you add, the spicy your eggs will be. Happy discovery!</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/08/spicy-noodles/?replytocom=70055#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-70055\", \"70055\", \"respond\", \"13143\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"comment-70114\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Andrea</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2012/08/spicy-noodles/#comment-70114\">10.17.12 at 4:08 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Used papperadelle for the noodles and coconut sugar for the brown sugar&#8230;I&#8217;m in heaven!</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/08/spicy-noodles/?replytocom=70114#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-70114\", \"70114\", \"respond\", \"13143\")'>Reply</a>\t\t