 wheat pasta I had in the fridge. Added a little more egg white to the one egg (hungry!) and eyeballed most of the sauce ingredients. Can I just say this is the best thing EVER? YUM. Oh, and I used agave syrup because I&#8217;m trying to stay away from sugar. Yep, worked just fine. So so so so so good. Thank you for this amazing recipe.</p>\n<p>And I love your blog. :-)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2012/08/spicy-noodles/?replytocom=71419#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-71419\", \"71419\", \"respond\", \"13143\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"comment-71475\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.blogger.com/profile/12470262687529516337' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Carina Robson</a></cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2012/08/spicy-noodles/#comment-71475\">01.10.13 at 7:49 am</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>I&#8217;ve made this two days in a row now and I love it! The first time, I cooked it exactly as the recipe stated. The second time, I did not use crushed pepper, used 1 tablespoon canola instead of the butter and doubled the soy sauce and sriracha which made it a little saucier, a little less sweet and gave it the perfect umami taste for me. Thanks so much for sharing the recipe!</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/